text: Prata is crispy and nicely cooked. $2.6 for 2 Plain. Nasi bryani mutton is cooked perfectly. Not too hard. Fish curry not too spicy.
chicken is too dry and expensive, 5 items Indian rojak cost $11?!? and the sauce is a bit too sweet. definitely not "king" standard food.

CAREFUL!!!!!!!!

Rice: $1.50
Mutton Soup: $6.00

Total: $7.50

Just a small bowl of soup charge $6.00, soup is not hot at all. Spring onions smells(not fresh). The rice alone cost $1.50 for a normal rice, which I can buy 3 bowls next stall at 50cent each.

Overall experience: Disappointed

For next Customer who ordering, please remember to ask him for the price first before you place an order. They do not key in cashier when they collect payment. Very dishonest. Shouting at other customers and being rude, another customer walked away after my order.

Halal indian muslim food, briyani is big portion and surprisingly good taste (disclaimer, though some days taste different). Prata and thosai taste good as well.

It’s quite nearby so it’s handy to get food from here. Alhamdulillah
Decided to get a plate of coin prata as the queue was constantly snaking which got me curious. took about 10min to get my order, tasted crispy and sweet! Not too bad.
